      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELEVENTH SCOTCH (7) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a slick early split, giving a sight but fading out of it to finish fourth (19.85) at Healesville over 350m. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in four starts. Ready to return to form. HARTLAND BONNIE (2) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (22.91) at Shepparton. Has a good record here at this journey. Should be about the money. TIGGY TOUCH (1) produced a moderate performance last time when sixth at Shepparton over 390m behind Paw Eden (22.93) in a Grade 5. Can figure in the finish. JARMON (8) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
